{
  "texts": [
    "Building on this foundation, we propose LMLCC-Net to enhance the prediction of lung nodule malignancy on CT images.",
    "It processes normalized CT scans by dividing the input into branches that learn and focus on specific intensity ranges corresponding to the CT Hounsfield Units.",
    "This design allows the model to capture richer spatial information and extract more representative features, ultimately improving its ability to differentiate between benign and malignant nodules.",
    "Our contributions demonstrate the effectiveness of combining innovative labeling techniques with advanced neural network architectures.",
    "The LMLCC-Net offers a promising tool for more accurate and reliable lung nodule classification, which could have significant implications for early cancer detection and patient outcomes.FIGURE 1.1FIGURE 1."
  ]
}